               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-274-person1506">
                  GEORGE 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1506" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1506" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1506" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prisoner's father; he lived with me. I have taken him several times from prison before - these articles were in a chest of drawers in my room; they were not locked. I went to bed with him on the 1st of April - he got up early the next morning, left me in bed, and took these things with him - I had seen them all safe in the afternoon.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Is there any marks on them? A. There was on the shirt; I know the ring by its general appearance.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-274-person1507">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JONES
               <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1507" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1507" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1507" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. The prisoner pawned a ring with me, in the name of Edward Palmer - I am certain of his person.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. How do you know me? A. I remember you very well - I made out the duplicate - I believe him to be the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-274-person1508">
                  CHARRES 
                  JACOBS
               <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1508" type="surname" value="JACOBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1508" type="given" value="CHARRES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1508" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner in Oxford-street one day, about the middle of April - he said, "Charles, I have the ticket of a nice shirt and handkerchief to sell;" he asked 1s. for them, and said he wanted the money<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182705310106"></xptr>then; I gave him 1s., went to the pawnbroker's, and go them out. Here they are.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-274-person1509">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1509" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1509" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1509" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On the 24th of April I took the prisoner in Adam and Eve-court. I found nothing on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-274-person1510">
                  HENRY 
                  RICHARD BUCKERIDGE
               <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1510" type="surname" value="RICHARD BUCKERIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1510" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-274-person1510" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Davis gave me the duplicate of a ring.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. It is false about my father's taking me out of prison. As he has come here to expose me, I think it my duty to expose him - he has been convicted here, and sentenced for fourteen years himself.</p>
               <p>GEORGE HARRISON. I was tried here for buying property, which I did not know was stolen, and received sentence of fourteen years' transportation.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270531-274-verdict1482" type="verdictDescription">
